      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "SPECIAL ROCKY (1) broke well and quickly mustered speed to win over the 350m at Q Straight two runs back then prominent throughout when finishing second at this track last start. One of the leading chances. CHAD POWERS (6) isn't a quick beginner but comes home hard and has run into the minors the last four start, the latest winding up strongly when third (25.88) in a Grade 5 at this track. Wound up strongly to place two back then did the same last time, finishing on late when third (25.88) in a Grade 5 at this track. Goes very well here finding the frame in each of three starts. Hard to beat again. SECRET STORY (8) turned in a plain performance last time when fifth at this track over 457m behind Boom Town (25.87) in a Grade 4/5. Was a winner the start prior. Key runner who gets his chance to atone. GOLDEN PHARAOH (4) recorded a 2.5 lengths win (21.80) in a Grade 5 last time at this track. Has two wins already from this draw.",
